This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual odometry systems. The use of multi-objective optimization and decision-making utility function suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper's focus on descriptor sharing and corner and pixel selection strategies suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's emphasis on real-time performance and efficient computation suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
